# Reproduce "respawned mech still has smoke" bug. Player takes damage
# (low limb HP) until smoke is emitting, dies, waits for respawn, and
# we capture frames around the respawn to see what FX persists.
#
# Smoke spawns at limb HP < 30% (simulate.c). To drive this we use a
# debug "damage" path — but there isn't one in shotmode. So instead
# we kill the mech with kill_peer which sets HP=0 (limb HP > 30% so
# no smoke from low-HP gating before death, but FX_STUMP and the
# 64-particle blood spray from mech_dismember fire on death). Then
# we wait the 180-tick respawn delay and check the respawned body.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/m6_ctf_respawn_fx
seed 1 2

map crossfire
mode ctf

# Park on the BLUE flag platform — small spawn island so respawn
# is likely to land back on the same RED platform.
spawn_at 600 1496

contact_sheet ctf_respawn_fx cols 4 cell 320 180

at 1 shot t01_pristine

# Kill the mech.
at 30 kill_peer 0
at 60 shot t60_dying_fx
at 120 shot t120_ragdoll_settling

# FX_STUMP duration is 1.5s = 90 ticks; FX_BLOOD up to 1.5s.
# So by tick 30+90+90 = 210, all death FX should be gone.
at 210 shot t210_pre_respawn_fx_cleared

# Respawn at tick 30 + 180 = 210.
at 215 shot t215_post_respawn_check
at 230 shot t230_post_respawn_settled
at 260 shot t260_post_respawn_late

at 300 end
